description.narrative: By the end of 2016, at least 80% of under five years children and 50% of new-borns in targeted localities are benefiting from integrated management of childhood illnesses (IMCI), essential new borne care, postnatal care and immunization services at health facility and community level (including Nationwide interventions).,which contributes to Child Health, Health And Emergencies, Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health, Protect, Care And Support Children And Families Affected By Hiv. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: At least 3.8 million of the most vulnerable children (girls and boys) including children affected by humanitarian crisis have access and use scaled-up proven sustainable, high impact, integrated quality services for life saving, learning, development and protection in the most deprived localities in Sudan.
